<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-42-0134 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper evaluates development of the Enterprise which coordinates railtransport in the Rybnik-Jastrzebie mine union and is a basis for theintegrated rail transport system from coal mines to coal preparationplants, coal fired power plants and to large spoil banks. The integratedsystem is used for coal transport and mineral waste transport from coalmines and for transport of sand used as packings in underground mining.The following aspects of system operation are discussed: design of railsystem, number of mines and coal consumer points, increasing length ofthe rail system, locomotives and railroad cars, communication systems,control systems, automatic traffic systems, railroad track maintenanceand repair in areas influenced by underground coal mining, reliabilityof transport equipment, personnel.</TEXT></DOC>